        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 9:54PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 954 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ashville, or 9 miles southeast of Oneonta, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ashville, Steele, Neely Henry Lake, Whitney Junction, Alabama
International Dragway, Neely Henry Dam, Caldwell, Horse Pens Forty,
and I 59 Rest Areas At Oneonta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for central,
northeastern and east central Alabama.</instruction>
